{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 03:24:42.421481", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nOverview\n- Topology: 2 leaves (leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1), 2 spines (spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1), 1 super-spine (super_spine_router_0), 2 hosts (pc_0_0 behind leaf_router_0_0 and pc_0_1 behind leaf_router_0_1). EBGP-only Clos fabric, /31 on inter-router links, leaves advertise 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24.\n- Current state: Fabric is partially healthy. Core and one leaf are fine; one leaf is isolated from the EBGP control-plane, breaking inter-subnet reachability for its attached host.\n\nDetected Anomalies\n1) End-to-end reachability broken between the two hosts:\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 100% loss with “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1 (gateway on leaf_router_0_0).\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: 100% loss with “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.0.1.1 (gateway on leaf_router_0_1).\n- Host NICs and default routes are correctly configured:\n  - pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1\n  - pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1\n\n2) BGP control-plane failure on leaf_router_0_0:\n- leaf_router_0_0 “show ip bgp summary”: all neighbors in Idle, never established; PfxRcd 0.\n- leaf_router_0_0 “show ip bgp neighbors”: Last reset “OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS” for all spine neighbors.\n- leaf_router_0_0 routing table has only connected routes (its own 10.0.0.0/24 and interconnect /31s), no BGP-learned routes.\n\n3) Core and the other leaf are healthy:\n- leaf_router_0_1: BGP sessions established to spines; full set of /24s learned; routes present via 172.16.1.2.\n- spines:\n  - spine_router_0_0: Established to super-spine and other leaves; but neighbor 172.16.1.1 (leaf_router_0_0) is Idle. Explicit log: “Notification sent (OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS)”.\n  - spine_router_0_1: Established to super-spine and other leaves; leaf_router_0_0 peering similarly not up.\n- super_spine_router_0: Established to spines; receiving prefixes as expected from healthy spines.\n\nFault Localization\n- Fault isolated to leaf_router_0_0’s BGP configuration and its EBGP sessions toward the spines.\n\nRoot Cause\n- BGP AS-number mismatch on leaf_router_0_0.\n  - leaf_router_0_0 running-config: router bgp 65800 (local AS = 65800).\n  - Spines are configured to peer with leaf_router_0_0 as AS 65200 (e.g., spine_router_0_0 neighbor 172.16.1.1 remote-as 65200).\n  - This mismatch causes the spines to send/leaf to receive “OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS,” preventing session establishment.\n  - Consequently, leaf_router_0_0 neither advertises 10.0.0.0/24 to the fabric nor learns any remote /24s, leading its host to return “Destination Net Unreachable” for off-subnet traffic. Conversely, other leaves (including leaf_router_0_1) have no route to 10.0.0.0/24.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- All traffic to/from 10.0.0.0/24 (pc_0_0) is isolated at L3:\n  - pc_0_0 cannot reach any other subnets.\n  - Other subnets cannot reach 10.0.0.0/24.\n- Rest of the fabric (spines, super-spine, and leaf_router_0_1) is healthy and exchanging routes normally.\n\nKey Evidence\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1.\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.0.1.1.\n- leaf_router_0_0:\n  - router bgp 65800 (mis-AS).\n  - All BGP neighbors Idle with “OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS.”\n  - IP route: only connected; no BGP routes.\n- spine_router_0_0:\n  - neighbor 172.16.1.1 remote-as 65200 (expected AS).\n  - Notification sent: “OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS.”\n- leaf_router_0_1 and spines show established sessions and populated routing tables otherwise.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 22430, "output_tokens": 3657, "total_tokens": 26087, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 22016}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2560}}}
